Question:
Website visitors tracking
Develop a line chart to track the daily number of visitors to a website over the last year, color 'midnightblue' for the line.
Matplotlib Color Mapping - color='midnightblue'
Matplotlib Figure Size - figsize=(14,7)

Data Dictionary:
Table name = 'df'
date: datetime64 (dt)
visitors: int64 (int)

Code:
**Attempt #1
# Import libraries:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Sort dates
df = df.sort_values("date")

# Set figure size
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 7))

# Create the plot
plt.plot(df["date"], df["visitors"], color='midnightblue')

# Add labels and title
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Visitors")
plt.title("Website Visitors Tracking")

# Rotate dates to prevent overlapping
plt.xticks(rotation=45)

# Ensure labels aren't truncated
plt.tight_layout()

plt.show()


**Solution #1 (set months for every tick only using matplotlib.pyplot)
# Import libraries:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Preview data and statistics
df.head(5)
df.describe().reset_index()

# Sort dates
df = df.sort_values("date")

# Set figure size
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 7))

# Group by year month and take the minimum date
monthly_ticks = df.groupby(df['date'].dt.to_period('M'))['date'].min()

# Create labels in 'YYYY-MM' format
monthly_labels = [d.strftime("%Y-%m") for d in monthly_ticks]

# Create the plot
plt.plot(df["date"], df["visitors"], color='midnightblue')

# Set ticks, labels, and rotate dates to prevent overlapping
plt.xticks(ticks=monthly_ticks, labels=monthly_labels, rotation=45)

# Add labels and title
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Visitors")
plt.title("Website Visitors Tracking")

# Ensure labels aren't truncated
plt.tight_layout()

plt.show()


**Solution #2 (set months for every tick with matplotlib.dates)
# Import libraries:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.dates as mdates

# Preview data:
df.head(5)

# Value Counts
df["date"].value_counts().reset_index(name="frequency")
df["visitors"].value_counts().reset_index(name="frequency")

# Sort dates
df = df.sort_values(by="date", ascending=True)

# Set figure and axes with figure size
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(14, 7))

# Create the plot
ax.plot(df["date"], df["visitors"], color='midnightblue')

# Set locator to show a tick for every month
ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(mdates.MonthLocator())

# Format the date
ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter("%b %Y"))

# Add labels and title
ax.set_xlabel("Month")
ax.set_ylabel("Visitors")
ax.set_title("Website visitors tracking")

# Rotate dates to prevent overlapping
plt.xticks(rotation=45)

# Ensure labels aren't truncated
plt.tight_layout()

plt.show()

